Customer ratings by feature

Additional details

The GE-branded UltraPro Window and Door Alarms provide a simple-to-use, cost-effective security solution to protect against home invasions. The 120-decibel alarms are loud enough to make a would-be intruder think twice about entering through your doors or windows. Each alarm features an easy-access chime/OFF/alarm switch. The straightforward design makes your security setup intuitive and streamlined. With no wires required for installation, protecting an entry point is as easy as mounting the alarm using the included double-sided tape. When a door or window is opened the alarms base becomes separated from its magnet, triggering a gentle chime or ringing alarm. Its even great for alerting you when other indoor areas, like cabinets and drawers, are accessed. Powered by four included LR44 batteries, the LED indicator on the front will notify you when power is low. This set of GE-branded UltraPro Personal Security Window and Door Alarms are perfect for homes, apartments, dorm rooms, offices, RVs, campers and much more.

Customers say

Customers find the window and door alarm works well, particularly for camper doors, and appreciate its effectiveness as a security measure, making them feel safe. The device is easy to install and offers good value for money, with one customer noting it works solidly through plastic edging. The loudness receives mixed feedback, with some finding it surprisingly loud while others note the chime doesn't sound repeatedly. The adhesive quality and battery life also get mixed reviews - while some say the adhesive is strong enough and the batteries last about 4-6 months, others report poor adhesion and short battery life.

  • Ickaris
    4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Effective Door Chime
    Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2016
    Size: 1 Pack
    This is an inexpensive and simple 3 way switch operation Door Chime/Alarm. Installation takes about 2-5 minutes per unit. A deeper look. First off, I feel this unit is best suited for it's Door Chime feature. For example, if a child is to open the... See more
    This is an inexpensive and simple 3 way switch operation Door Chime/Alarm. Installation takes about 2-5 minutes per unit.

    A deeper look.
    First off, I feel this unit is best suited for it's Door Chime feature.
    For example, if a child is to open the door and walk outside, you will know. It gives a loud double chime sound the moment the door opens, but then goes silent. ( Effective alert system, but doesn't remind you to close the door. )

    The Alarm feature is extremely loud and continuous from the time the door opens and until the door is closed. It's very similar to the sound of a residential fire alarm. If an intruder gets the door open, it may be enough to startle them and send them running. Or- Perhaps, to a seasoned thief, or intruder of some sort, they may continue to come inside and shut the door and the alarm will shut off immediately. If the intruder identified the source, they could easily locate the on/off switch, or the battery compartment door to disable the unit. ( At best, this unit may provide you precious moments to grab a weapon so you can defend your family and or property in the case the unfortunate event occurs. )

    ****So dollar for dollar, It's a small, but wise investment. I'd say this is well worth the money depending on the purpose you intend to use this unit for. **** I chose to give 4 stars for lacking volume control and additional double backed tape for instances where door molding effects mounting position, creating an unlevel surface. A couple of my doors have molding which create a 1/4 inch gap. I resolved this issue by purchasing additional double backed tape for the smaller strip side to level the slope off of the molding and then foam tape for the Chime side to raise it to the appropriate height. I had to get slightly creative, but these additional steps only added a couple extra minutes to the installation time.
    ( Hopefully the manufacturer takes note and adds these additional items to their package. )

    To answer several questions you may have -

    Can these be used outside? *NO Not designed for outdoor use
    The unit must be mounted somewhere on the opening side of the door. I recommend near the top corner out of reach of children.
    Would I use it on a fridge or freezer? *No, read above^
    Will it work on certain doors or windows? In most cases, I'd say you can make it work using additional double backed tape and or foam tape.
    Battery operated - LR44G batteries X4
    Can these sync with current Alarm systems? *No
    Can these sync with each other? *No
    Will the Alarm feature make you go def? *Possibly ;)
    Can your neighbors hear the alarm from across the street? *Yes, while the door is open, anyone in the area will here the alarm and quite possibly the chime as well.

    3.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    HOPEFULLY THIS DOESN'T HAPPEN TO YOU...
    Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2025
    Size: 12 Pack
    I would have given these a five-star rating if this hadn't happened: I bought the 12 pack, to have enough for all the windows. So I installed them all, the day they arrived. That night, at 5 a.m. the alarm on one of my bedroom windows went off. It's extremely... See more
    I would have given these a five-star rating if this hadn't happened: I bought the 12 pack, to have enough for all the windows. So I installed them all, the day they arrived. That night, at 5 a.m. the alarm on one of my bedroom windows went off. It's extremely loud, and extremely jarring, to say the least, when it happens when you're sound asleep.
    I stopped it, and reset it, and attempted to go back to sleep. At six O'clock it went off again. I turned it off and left it off.
    To be clear, the window had not been moved in the slightest. The next day I checked the batteries to make sure it wasn't simply a matter of weak batteries, but that wasn't the case. There's a button you press to check the batteries, and it lit up the tester light green. Having malfunctioned twice, and cost me several hours sleep, it went into the garbage can. It's not going to have another chance to do it again, and I'm certain it would have. I was just glad it happened to me, and not another member of the family, because it would have scared them out of their wits. So instead of a 12 pack, I got an 11 pack for my money.
    Consequently, I now have serious doubts about the other eleven. Are they eventually going to go off for no reason and scare the hell out of my family? Are they even going to work correctly, if there's an actual break-in attempt?
    Basically, I now have zero confidence in these. The best I can say is, they aren't very expensive, and they are loud enough to wake the dead. I thought of GE products as being well-made, but I won't be buying any more of their brand.

  • Barrowfordian
    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Easy to Install and Use
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on August 19, 2023
    I live in a somewhat remote rural area, and in a house with a number of downstairs windows and doors. For security reasons, and following some minor thefts in other properties nearby, I needed either a full alarm system or individual alarms for windows and doors. I saw... See more
    I live in a somewhat remote rural area, and in a house with a number of downstairs windows and doors. For security reasons, and following some minor thefts in other properties nearby, I needed either a full alarm system or individual alarms for windows and doors. I saw these, and thought I would give them a try. There are two parts to each alarm - the main alarm and a smaller, magnetised piece that fits on either the door/window or door/window frame. The parts are attached to window/door by the supplied double sided sticky patch (this is a surprisingly strong bonding sticky patch, and I have no doubt it will remain in place for some time). The two pieces of the alarm shoould be attached in such a way that there is a narrow gap between the two parts. To turn the alarm on one simply moves the side switch on the main alarm piece down as far as it will go. (Moving it half way down gives a single chime when the door/window is opened). To turn off the alarm simply close the window/door, or physically move the switch to the 'off' position. The alarm itself is quite loud (110 - 120 decibels - I have seen both quoted in literature and on the box! Whatever it is, it's loud!) This package, with 12 alarms for 50 (the price I paid) has turned out to be good value as far as meeting what I needed, the ease of installation and the noise each alarm makes when triggered; as such I can recommend them. (These are my own thoughts on an item I have bought myself and found useful.)
    I live in a somewhat remote rural area, and in a house with a number of downstairs windows and doors.
